The British High Commission organised with the Cayman Islands Government to have a special charter flight stop in Nassau on its way to London on Tuesday 28 July. No further charter flights are planned. See commercial travel below for alternative options.
Commercial travel
Flight availability is restricted and subject to change, limited international flights and domestic flights are available while the state of emergency remains in force. Private charter flight options are also available, these may require the prior approval of the Bahamas Civil Aviation Authority. Approval requests should be submitted to: covid19@bcaa.com.
There is currently no direct commercial air travel to and from The Bahamas to the UK. British Airways plan to resume flights in late October. This is subject to change. Please refer to the BA website and call centre +1 877 767 7970 for more information. Arrival and departure via transit destinations such as Canada or the US may be possible for eligible travellers. You should refer to the travel advice and restrictions before travelling.
The situation and rules vary across the islands. Guidelines on inter-island travel, including testing, travel health cards, and quarantine requirements are available in the latest Emergency Orders from the Office of the Prime Minister
Details of the procedures travel health card for domestic travel are available here.
Returning to the UK
When you return, you must follow the rules for entering the UK.
If you cannot leave Bahamas
If you cannot leave Bahamas at this time, see advice on staying in Bahamas during coronavirus
